gameRecap.title: Game Recap: Pacers 125, Knicks 111
gameRecap.excerpt: The Pacers defeated the Knicks, 125-111. Myles Turner led the way for the Pacers with 23 points (9-9 FG, 2-2 3pt. FG), along with eight rebounds and four assists, while Tyrese Haliburton added 22 points and 12 assists in the victory. Jalen Brunson tallied 39 points (14-25 FG) for the Knicks in the losing effort. The Pacers improve to 30-24 on the season, while the Knicks fall to 33-20.
